-- European shares inch down ahead of data
-- By Lionel Laurent
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 03:20AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, June 3 (Reuters) - European shares gave up some of their recent gains in early trade on Tuesday ahead of fresh inflation and unemployment data from the eurozone.

Technology and telecommunications stocks, including Finland's Nokia <NOK1V.HE>, Sweden's Ericsson <ERICb.ST> and France's ALcatel-Lucent <ALUA.PA>, were among the worst performers on the pan-European FTSEurofirst 300 <.FTEU3>, down 0.2 percent By 0716 GMT. The UK FTSE 100 <.FTSE>, France's CAC 40 <.FCHI> and Germany's DAX <.GDAXI> were down between 0.1 and 0.2 percent.